                        2020</ref>)</sourceNote><section id="ID_1438403253159_003" name="s1" reason="inEffect" role="rule" startPeriod="2021-02-18" status="operational" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><heading>Fees payable in Court</heading><subsection id="ID_1438412679270_012" name="1" temporalId="s1_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content>The fees specified in the <ref>Schedule</ref> are payable in connection with an appeal in the Court in respect of the matters specified.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1438412679270_020" name="2" temporalId="s1_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>The Registrar may reduce, remit or defer payment of a fee in any particular case if he thinks fit and where he does so shall endorse on the relevant document a note of the reduction, remission or deferment and the reason therefor.</content></subsection></section><section id="ID_1438403253175_001" name="s2" reason="inEffect" role="rule" startPeriod="2021-02-18" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Method of payment</heading><content>Fees shall be paid by means of adhesive stamps or by franking the relevant document.</content></section><section id="ID_1438403253175_003" name="s3" reason="inEffect" role="rule" startPeriod="2021-02-18" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Application to HKSAR Government</heading><content>These Rules apply to proceedings by or against the Government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.</content></section><section id="ID_1438403253190_001" name="s4" reason="inEffect" role="rule" startPeriod="2021-02-18" status="operational" temporalId="s4"><num value="4">4.</num><heading>Transitional provision relating to the Hong Kong Court of Final Appeal Fees
            (Amendment) <ref>Rules 2009</ref></heading><leadIn>Where a party entitled to require any costs to be taxed has obtained an appointment
